File extensions map

Source: R/load.R, R/save.R
loadFiles.Rd

How to load various types of files in R.

This function has two roles:

  1. to proceed with the loading of files that are in a simList; or

  2. as a shortcut to simInit(inputs = filelist).

A data.frame with information on how to load various types of files in R, containing the columns:

  • exts: the file extension;

  • fun: the function to use for files with this file extension;

  • package: the package from which to load fun.

.fileExtensions()

loadFiles(sim, filelist, ...)

# S4 method for simList,missing
loadFiles(sim, filelist, ...)

# S4 method for missing,ANY
loadFiles(sim, filelist, ...)

# S4 method for missing,missing
loadFiles(sim, filelist, ...)

.saveFileExtensions()

Arguments

sim

simList object.

filelist

list or data.frame to call loadFiles directly from the filelist as described in Details

...

Additional arguments.

Value

data.frame of file extension, package, and function mappings

the modified sim, invisibly.

data.frame

Note

Generally not intended to be used by users.

See also

inputs()

Author

Eliot McIntire and Alex Chubaty

Examples

# \donttest{
library(SpaDES.core)

# Load random maps included with package
filelist <- data.frame(
  files = dir(getMapPath(tempdir()), full.names = TRUE),
  functions = "rasterToMemory",
  package = "SpaDES.core"
)
sim1 <- loadFiles(filelist = filelist) # loads all the maps to sim1 simList
#> Setting:
#>   options(
#>     reproducible.cachePath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/reproducible/cache'
#>     spades.inputPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/inputs'
#>     spades.outputPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/outputs'
#>     spades.modulePath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/modules'
#>     spades.scratchPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/scratch'
#>   )
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit Using setDTthreads(1). To change: 'options(spades.DTthreads = X)'.
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit DEM read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/DEM.tif using rasterToMemory
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit forestAge read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/forestAge.tif using rasterToMemory
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit forestCover read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/forestCover.tif using rasterToMemory
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit habitatQuality read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/habitatQuality.tif using rasterToMemory
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit percentPine read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/percentPine.tif using rasterToMemory
#> Elpsed time for simInit: 0.1556411 secs

# Second, more sophisticated. All maps loaded at time = 0, and the last one is reloaded
#  at time = 10 and 20 (via "intervals").
# Also, pass the single argument as a list to all functions...
#  specifically, when add "native = TRUE" as an argument to the raster function
files <- dir(getMapPath(tempdir()), full.names = TRUE)
arguments <- I(rep(list(lyrs = 1), length(files)))
filelist <- data.frame(
   files = files,
   functions = "terra::rast",
   objectName = NA,
   arguments = arguments,
   loadTime = 0,
   intervals = c(rep(NA, length(files)-1), 10)
)

sim2 <- loadFiles(filelist = filelist) # only does the time = 0 loading; see next
#> Setting:
#>   options(
#>     reproducible.cachePath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/reproducible/cache'
#>     spades.inputPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/inputs'
#>     spades.outputPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/outputs'
#>     spades.modulePath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/modules'
#>     spades.scratchPath = '/tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/SpaDES/scratch'
#>   )
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit Using setDTthreads(1). To change: 'options(spades.DTthreads = X)'.
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit DEM read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/DEM.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit forestAge read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/forestAge.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit forestCover read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/forestCover.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit habitatQuality read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/habitatQuality.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit percentPine read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/percentPine.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Elpsed time for simInit: 0.05760813 secs
end(sim2) <- 10
sim2 <- spades(sim2) # loads the object at time 10
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit Using setDTthreads(1). To change: 'options(spades.DTthreads = X)'.
#> Nov09 16:31:43 chckpn:init total elpsd: 0.059 secs | 0 checkpoint init 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 save  :init total elpsd: 0.06 secs | 0 save init 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 prgrss:init total elpsd: 0.061 secs | 0 progress init 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :init total elpsd: 0.063 secs | 0 load init 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs total elpsd: 0.064 secs | 10 load inputs 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs percentPine read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/percentPine.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs    at time 10
#> simList saved in
#> SpaDES.core:::.pkgEnv$.sim
#> It will be deleted at next spades() call.

# if we extend the end time and continue running, it will load an object scheduled
#  at time = 10, and it will also schedule a new object loading at 20 because
#  interval = 10
end(sim2) <- 20
sim2 <- spades(sim2) # loads the percentPine map 2 more times, once at 10, once at 20
#> Nov09 16:31:43 simInit Using setDTthreads(1). To change: 'options(spades.DTthreads = X)'.
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs total elpsd: 0.081 secs | 20 load inputs 0
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs percentPine read from /tmp/RtmpLrHPqR/maps/percentPine.tif using rast(inMemory=FALSE)
#> Nov09 16:31:43 load  :inputs    at time 20
#> simList saved in
#> SpaDES.core:::.pkgEnv$.sim
#> It will be deleted at next spades() call.
# }
